      • requestAllData

        public java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.lang.Void> requestAllData()
        Description copied from interface: CustomEmoji
        Asynchrounously requests all data about the CustomEmoji, so that future requesting tasks will complete instantly. Use this method if you want to acquire a lot of CustomEmoji data soon, and block the thread using CompletableFuture.join() upon calling this method. That way all future requests on this CustomEmoji object like CustomEmoji.requestCreator() can be instantly used CompletableFuture.get(), or you can simply use the non-requesting methods from then on, like CustomEmoji.getCreator(). The returning future may be completed instantly, as the CustomEmoji might already be initialized with all data.
        Specified by:
        requestAllData in interface CustomEmoji
        Returns:
        A future that completes with null when all data has been recieved.

      • requestIsAnimated

        public java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<java.lang.Boolean> requestIsAnimated()
        Description copied from interface: CustomEmoji
        Performs a request to acquire whether this emoji is animated. If there has been any request that includes this data made already, the returned future is completed instantly, and you can use CustomEmoji.isAnimated() instead. The method CustomEmoji.toDiscordPrintable() always requires to know whether the emoji is animated, so it always performs a blocking request on this method. This means, after calling CustomEmoji.toDiscordPrintable(), this method will always be completed once.
        Specified by:
        requestIsAnimated in interface CustomEmoji
        Returns:
        A future to contain whether the emoji is animated.
